s.t: import { useState, useEffect, useRef } from "react";type Particle = {  id: string;  x: number;  y: number;  velocity: [number, number];  opacity: number;};export default function AmbientField() {  const canvasRef = useRef<HTMLCanvasElement>(null);  const [particles, setParticles] = useState<Particle[]>([]);  useEffect(() => {    const canvas = canvasRef.current;    if (!canvas) return;    const ctx = canvas.getContext("2d");    let animationFrame: number;    function generate(count: number) {      return Array.from({ length: count }).map((_, i) => ({        id: `p-${i}-${Date.now()}`,        x: Math.random() * canvas.width,        y: Math.random() * canvas.height,        velocity: [Math.random() - 0.5, Math.random() - 0.5],        opacity: Math.random() * 0.8 + 0.2      }));    }    setParticles(generate(120));    function update() {      if (!ctx) return;      ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);      particles.forEach(p => {        p.x += p.velocity[0];        p.y += p.velocity[1];        ctx.globalAlpha = p.opacity;        ctx.fillStyle = "#7df9ff";        ctx.fillRect(p.x, p.y, 2, 2);      });      animationFrame = requestAnimationFrame(update);    }    update();    return () => cancelAnimationFrame(animationFrame);  }, []);  return <canvas ref={canvasRef} width={800} height={600} />;}
